🧠 What is File Upload?

File upload means:

👉 Sending files (images, videos, docs) from client → server

Examples:

✔ Profile picture upload
✔ Resume upload
✔ Product images

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

🔷 How File Upload Works?

```text id="flow1"
Client (Form)
   ↓
multipart/form-data
   ↓
Server (Express + Multer)
   ↓
Store File (disk/cloud)
```

---

🔷 What is Multer?

**Multer** is a middleware for:

👉 Handling `multipart/form-data` (file uploads)

✔ Works with Express
✔ Easy to use
✔ Supports multiple files

---

🔷 Install Multer

```bash id="cmd1"
npm install multer
```

---

🔷 Basic Setup

```javascript id="code1"
const express = require("express");
const multer = require("multer");

const app = express();

const upload = multer({ dest: "uploads/" });
```

---

🔷 Upload Single File

```javascript id="code2"
app.post("/upload", upload.single("file"), (req, res) => {
  res.send("File uploaded successfully");
});
```

---

🔷 HTML Form Example

```html id="html1"
<form action="/upload" method="POST" enctype="multipart/form-data">
  <input type="file" name="file" />
  <button type="submit">Upload</button>
</form>
```

---

🔷 Upload Multiple Files

```javascript id="code3"
app.post("/upload-multiple", upload.array("files", 5), (req, res) => {
  res.send("Multiple files uploaded");
});
```

---

🔷 File Information

```javascript id="code4"
console.log(req.file);   // single file
console.log(req.files);  // multiple files
```

---

🔷 Custom Storage (Best Practice ⭐)

```javascript id="code5"
const storage = multer.diskStorage({
  destination: (req, file, cb) => {
    cb(null, "uploads/");
  },
  filename: (req, file, cb) => {
    cb(null, Date.now() + "-" + file.originalname);
  }
});

const upload = multer({ storage });
```

---

🔷 File Filter (Security)

```javascript id="code6"
const fileFilter = (req, file, cb) => {
  if (file.mimetype === "image/png" || file.mimetype === "image/jpeg") {
    cb(null, true);
  } else {
    cb(null, false);
  }
};

const upload = multer({ storage, fileFilter });
```

---

🔷 File Size Limit

```javascript id="code7"
const upload = multer({
  storage,
  limits: { fileSize: 1024 * 1024 * 2 } // 2MB
});
```

---

🔷 Serving Uploaded Files

```javascript id="code8"
app.use("/uploads", express.static("uploads"));
```

Access:

```text id="url1"
/uploads/file-name.jpg
```

